quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  7,96,"Had the people of the towns believed and turned righteous, We would have opened for them the blessings of the heaven and the earth; but they rejected the truth, so We seized them by what they were doing"
  7,97,"Do the people of the towns feel secure that Our might will not come upon them by night, while they sleep"
  7,98,"Do the people of the towns feel secure that Our might will not come upon them by day, while they play"
  7,99,Do they feel safe from God’s plan? None feel safe from God’s plan except the losing people
  7,100,"Is it not guidance for those who inherit the land after its inhabitants, that if We willed, We could strike them for their sins? And seal up their hearts, so that they would not hear"
  7,101,"These towns—We narrate to you some of their tales. Their messengers came to them with the clear signs, but they would not believe in what they had rejected previously. Thus God seals the hearts of the disbelievers"
  7,102,We found most of them untrue to their covenants; We found most of them corrupt
  7,103,"Then, after them, We sent Moses with Our miracles to Pharaoh and his establishment, but they denounced them. So consider the end of the evildoers"
  7,104,"Moses said, “O Pharaoh, I am a messenger from the Lord of the Worlds.”"